Prosper Loan Data Exploration¶

by Hind Al Ramah¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This data set contains 113,937 records of loans along with 81 variables on each loan, such as loan amount, interest rate, borrower income, and many others. Our exploration will foucs on only 10 to 13 variables.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The data set contains 113,937 records of loans along with 81 variables on each loan. After dropping some irrelevant features of our investigation, we have only 46 variables. The data set includes 31 float, 4 int, and 11 object variables.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main features we will investigate in this project are associated directly with answering the following questions:

  • What factors affect users ability to get a loan?
  • What factors impact a high prosper loan risk?
  • What features affects the borrowers APR or interest rate?
  • Are there differences between loans depending on how large the original loan amount was?

These answers associated with many features but mainly 'CreditGrade', 'Term','BorrowerAPR', 'InterestRate', 'ProsperRatingAlpha', 'LoanStatus' and 'LoanOriginalAmount'.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The rest of the features will support in our primary investigation such as 'MonthlyLoanPayment', 'IncomeRange', 'EstimatedLoss' , 'BorrowerState', 'ProsperRatingNumeric' and more.

# replace categories
df.LoanStatus.replace(('Past Due (1-15 days)','Past Due (31-60 days)', 'Past Due (61-90 days)','Past Due (16-30 days)'
                       ,'Past Due (91-120 days)', 'Past Due (>120 days)')
                      ,('Past Due'), inplace=True)

df.LoanStatus.replace(('FinalPaymentInProgress'),('Current'), inplace=True)

# drop cancelled records
df = df[df.LoanStatus != 'Cancelled']

LoanOriginalAmount vs MonthlyLoanPayment¶

In [44]:
plt.figure(figsize = [12, 10])
bin_size = 0.25
xbin_edges = np.arange(0.5, df['LoanOriginalAmount'].max()+bin_size, bin_size)
xbin_centers = (xbin_edges + bin_size/2)[:-1]

# compute each bin
data_xbins = pd.cut(df['LoanOriginalAmount'], xbin_edges, right = False, include_lowest = True)
y_means = df['MonthlyLoanPayment'].groupby(data_xbins).mean()
y_sems = df['MonthlyLoanPayment'].groupby(data_xbins).sem()

# error bar represent the amount of data by points
plt.errorbar(x = xbin_centers, y = y_means, yerr = y_sems)
plt.title('Loan Original Amount VS Monthly Payment line graph(Mean)')
plt.xlabel('Loan Original Amount ($)')
plt.ylabel('Monthly Payment ($)');

The line graph above represents the mean of the original amount of loans with monthly payment rate. The plot has a healthy trend line, the monthly payment amount increases as the amount of the orignal loan get higher. To resolve the higher monthly payment amount, first borrower has to minimize the amount of original loan amount; secondly, they should extend the term of the loan for example from 3 years to 5.

To conclude the 1 year period loan had the lowest interest rate among all quarters as shown in the above graph.
